<li id="lithub_daily_widget-9" class="widget widget_lithub_daily_widget"><div class="lithub-daily-header"><a href="/category/lit-hub-daily/"><b>Lithub</b> Daily</a></div><h2 class="widgettitle">August 5, 2024</h2>
<a href="https://lithub.com/lit-hub-daily-august-5-2024/"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-241132 size-thumbnail" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Cornell_University_1987_Commencement_Schoellkopf_Field-150x150.jpg" alt="college Kenneth C. Zirkel, CC BY-SA 4.0 &lt;https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0&gt;, via Wikimedia Commons" width="150" height="150" /></a>
<ul>
 	<li><a href="https://thebaffler.com/latest/freedom-from-dissent-jindia" class="external" target="_blank"><span style="font-weight: 400">The independence of public universities is under attack, writes Shilpa Jindia</span></a></li>
 	<li><a href="https://www.tcj.com/flying-colors-comics/?utm_source=rss&amp;utm_medium=rss&amp;utm_campaign=flying-colors-comics" class="external" target="_blank">The state of comics publishing and sales</a></li>
 	<li><a href="https://www.newyorker.com/culture/open-questions/what-dont-we-know" class="external" target="_blank"><span style="font-weight: 400">The benefits of studying our ignorance</span></a></li>
</ul>
